caption: Was very much looking forward to the good. The salad was fresh but the pasta was chewy and stick together. The pizza was not seasoned and not cooked long enough. It only took 10/15 minutes to get the food. Think they should spend time cultivating their craft before want to charge 20 bucks for a pasta dish that could have been made by an armature. The calamari is not worth it either.
Great food, good lunch menu (love the grilled veggie panini), great dinner options (gnocchi, desserts, etc), but the best part is the free, fresh baked bread 👌🏾

I eat here often. Very familiar with the area because I grew up here. This restaurant is relatively new to the neighborhood. The food is good. Nice size and great ambiance. The owner is usually there and  he is very cordial and friendly. He will definitely remember you if you are a repeat customer. I do mostly takeout now because of the pandemic. The pizza pie is great for one person and the brick oven taste is awesome. Love the mashed potatoes. Be ready to spend but worth it.
Delicious food and great service
My daughter and I love this place! It’s our secret spot!!! Food it’s delicious!!
Sucked...as always, no matter how many times I try 😑
Wood oven pizza! Fun owner and waiters, good wine

WHAT A RISTORANTE.  Not only the owner and waiters are soooooo passionate about their food, their service. Their happiness and positivity lights up the entire neighborhood!! I have lived in NJ for the longest time, tho I haven't been to Italy, I thought our pasta were pretty good. Until I went to this place. THE BEST PASTA IN MY LIFE. And ask around you'd know I'm very harsh on food especially on seasoning and the food quality. But this restaurant leaves me no place to say anything but BRAVO, BUONA. A must go if you ever visit the upper part of NYC. Not only we have the art and music here, we have fantastic restaurants too!!
Good was great

The steak was something that seemed to be a slab of Salisbury Steak... you know the boxes kind... and the mash that was a side,  that was totally boxed mashed potatoes! Not ever going back, not worth $28.
Was there during Cuomo/Blasio ban on indoor dining. So they set up sidewalk tables. Very nice and urban experience with elevated NY subway tracks above. Great food and cocktailals.
The « pizza » arrived cold with almost no toppings (e.g. One out of four pieces had mushrooms, almost no cheese and sausage). The ravioli was also cold and tasteless.
Cold pizza. There is a difference between thin crust and no crust at all. You needed imagination to find cheese on the pizza.  And finally 17 usd for 5 ravioli.
Best pizza in the world
Best pizza!
Very nice place and good food.  Staff are wonderful and we enjoyed every meal
Delicious Polenta

The restaurant is next to the subway, with the noise, but it reminded us of Paris and the subway there when it is above ground level. It feels a bit like Clichy or Pigalle. The pizza and calamari were good. The margarita was generous.
Complete disregard of covid-19 precautions. Servers not wearing masks. They even opened inside space. Food is okay, definitely not worth getting the virus for.
Good atmosphere
Nice eatery.  Interesting menu.  Great service.  Reasonable prices.  Great desserts.

Great place (ambience and personnel). Excellent pizza (margherita, funghi) and most of all it is well cooked and never burnt. Delightful lentil soup and salads. Prices are reasonable. I go there frequently and never get disappointed.

Pleasant and cozy family restaurant located on Broadway and W 123rd St. Their food is fresh and seasoned evenly. The service when me and my family went was prompt and impeccable. This is also a nice place for a date night. The lighting is dim and ambiance is inviting.
Steak was perfect. Servers are probably from Italy and it’s so authentic. But there is c-fee for byob, it doesn’t bother me I just expected to be served. They just opened it😂

(Translated by Google) Christmas meal 2019 with the family: after leaving Christmas Mass, we were looking for a friendly place where to dine, the chance of walking made us enter this restaurant with pleasant surroundings: 4 people with big teens, well received by a young team, excellent pizzas and drinks at an affordable price. The servers offer, but do not force consumption, everyone takes what they want. I recommend carefree  (Original) Repas de Noël 2019 en famille: en sortant de la messe de Noël, nous recherchions un endroit convivial où dîner, le hasard de la marche nous a fait enter dans ce restaurant aux abords agréables :à 4 avec dqe grands ados, bien reçus par une équipe jeune, pizzas excellentes et boissons à un prix abordables. Les serveurs proposent, mais ne forcent pas à la consommation, chacun prend ce qu'il souhaite,. Je recommande sans souci
Lovely hidden gem of a restaurant. Friendly staff and good Italian fare
Bettolona is D Italian place in NYC, Sandro the owner is super  nice and  friendly, food is amazing and I expensive.... what else you need !!!

Lovely, well sized, charming Italian eatery right off the 125th 1 train stop. The food was great, the place was bustling and the service was appreciated. Good place to meet friends or eat as a family or couple - it’s neither super fancy or totally casual but a nice in between. Would eat here again if in the area and recommend it to friends.
Really love this place, owner is active and really cares about the customer experience.  Food is authentic and fantastic.
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelenteese
Very good food, the servings were a bit too small, but the service was great
Best Brick oven pizza

An EXCELLENT accident wss the result of our group lunch here at Betteolona as our destination was closed for lunch . Without hesitation, the manager WELCOMED our group of six , accomodated the walker and kept his CHARM throughout our epic feast !!! As you munch the fresh bread dipped in olive oil you may notice the staff adding wood to the woodburning stove and then recognize THAT distinct flavor in every bite. No rush, you have been transported to a charming cozy oasis in THIS hectic city !! Treat yourself ,join a few pals and savor the fresh simple flavors , fired breads and desserts to share !!! Who needs plane fare ...when you have Bettolona !!!!
Really good food!
Great service AMAAAAZING seafood spaghetti dish. Magnifico!
Incredibly kind and funny waiters. Will definitely come back
A friendly place and everything was delicious! Thanks!
Great pizza
Delicious food with great specials, attentive service
Best!
Food was incredible, service was genuine. All around a fantastic experience!! Highly recomend you go here if you are visiting NYC or are a resident.
Very good food, from the pasta dishes to the pizza, everything very well cooked.
Wonderful food
Excellent food. The pasta was amazing. Very friendly staff and owner.

I usually have complaints about the pasta served in the US. It's usually overcooked and has no concept of al dente. But this place was different.  One of my local friends recommended it and I casually stopped by for lunch. I ordered Bolognese. I didn't mean to test the restaurant, but they say you should try Bolognese to see if the restaurant is good or bad. Their Bolognese tasted fantastic. The pasta was perfect for me.  I wish more restaurants in the US were authentically Italian like this restaurant. Grazie, Bettolona!
Great food, great ambiance, great service.
Really like this authentic Italian restautant. Great service, delicious food. Simple but very good!! Healthy but very tasty! Options are very good!! Enjoy!!
Very good food and very friendly staff for decently priced proper Italian food
Nice Happy Hour!
A great, homey restaurant with a genuine Italian feel and amazing food. The staff are nice and professional, as well.
Like family. The food is good, the prices are good, and the service is great. Now that Sandro has Davide to help with the day-to-day, there's never a bad time to be here.

Decent Italian restaurant. Server was less helpful in explaining dishes than I would have hoped. Almost made up for by the delicious bread and fantastic pizza, which is not, despite what they may tell you, personal sized. Probably a good amount for 1.5 people each.

Pizza was ok, but mostly empty. I prefer Italian like pizzas that are not so full of toppings that you can't even put in your mouth, but this was ridiculous. It was supposed to have parmesan shavings and arugula. it had 5 small slices of cheese and no more that 10leaves of arugula. That was a mostly tomato pizza. The pasta was also dissapointing. Won't be coming back.
The food is good will come back
I used to love going here because all the food was made fresh, even though it took a long time. But now they have started microwaving the pasta, it's not so good any more.
Absolute garbage. This place sent a cold, smushed pizza and overpriced tiramisu.
Incredibly warm environment,  great food. The most effusive host!
Messed up my entire order (missed my potatoes ) and I couldn't go back again , I told them the incident and they didn't seem to care  .
Good ambience, music, service, poor vegetarian options
Wonderful wonderful staff

this is by far the BEST PIZZA AND ITALIAN FOOD in New York. I almost feel myself in Italy. The staff is friendly and welcoming. The restaurant offers clean, modern and cozy space for comfortable dive into Italian gastronomy.
Great neighborhood mainstay!
Great pastas at a great price. Love the tiramisu
A very good pizza.
I love the neighborhood feel of this place. The brick oven and good food are nice without a trip downtown.
We were there with a diverse group from church and they accommodated us really well.  Service and food were both very good.  We had a couple small mishaps but they recovered well.

(Translated by Google) Well cooked Italian dishes. Kind owner who converse pleasantly with customers. Correct prices.  (Original) Piatti italiani ben cucinati. Gentile il proprietario che conversa piacevolmente con i clienti. Prezzi corretti.
Excellent...

I went there for university social. Definitely not a place to handle that kind of an event. Otherwise, it seemed nice as a family dining place. We had meatballs, fried calamari which were nice. However, veggie hot pockets and veggie pizza were average at the most.
Great food in a wonderful atmosphere.  The service was amazing.  If you're in the upper west side I highly recommend it!
One of the worst pizzas I have ever had in NYC. It was burnt and tasteless. If it wasn't because of its vibe I would probably give it one star. I am  not sure why it has a good rating on Google...
Great pizza.  Friendly staff.
Gastronomic ecstasy.  Simple, artfully prepared, delicious.
A favorite spot when in the area
Very nice place...become my friends meeting point.
Delicious pizza and Italian food. Right by the #1 train
Great pizza and great atmosphere. However its pasta is not so great. I tried twice but both were mediocre. Pizza is great.

The food is good and the place is nice but the service is not good at all, the waiters are too slow, you should tell them each thing twice (eg. If you want some bread or if you need you water glass refilled), also the waiters do not have good interaction with the costumers, its not bad but it is just like they want you not to be there.
The service is very personal and friendly and the food is delicious for the price!
Wonderful meal and delightful people throughout the restaurant.
A neighborhood restaurant where groups meet. The owner greets everyone, including children, with a warm hello. The food is fresh and amazing, all while being reasonably priced.
(Translated by Google) Very good pizza, nice owner!  (Original) Pizza buonissima, propretario simpatico!
Great food!

Fantastic place with amazing food. Sandro the owner will make you feel like in italy. The pizza is an absolute must. Great selection of wine by the glass. Great ambiance and very reasonable prices. A must try.

Bettolona came well recommended by family, and it didn't disappoint. The space is cozy yet fun, and the service is very good. But the food is the star here. Between the exceptional wine recommendation, the delicious soup and an outstanding Margherita pizza, I wouldn't hesitate to come back next time that I am in town.
Great happy hour and staff.
Absolutely mental to eat here when you have two Italian powerhouses so close by in Pisticci and Max Soha

My girlfriend, her grandpa, and I celebrated her graduation from Columbia here and had just a pleasant time. Mid-upscale Italian is a good way to describe Bettolona. Casual, inviting atmosphere with a relaxing, coffee shop meets quiet bar vibe and some really excellent food that’s just a little more expensive than I’d want to pay for dinner on a normal night. Fettuccini, spinach lasagna, pizza blanche, an arugula salad, and three glasses of Italian beer. A good meal.

Ordered take out once and when I got home I realized they forgot the dessert (live less a block away). When I went back to ask for it they demanded I bring the entire order back to prove that they actually did forget the dessert. When I brought it back the manager (might have been owner) accused me of being a liar and said that he is doing me a favor and will overlook the extra dessert.  At best, it was condescending and demeaning. At worst, I can't prove it was racism, but it definitely felt like it.  The food is overpriced for the quality as well. So definitely not worth your money.

My favorite thing to do at Bettalona is grab a corner table, snuggle up to my spouse, drink some espresso, and munch on tiramisu as I look lovingly into his eyes. It's one of my favorite weekday date spots - romantic and a good price point on food and wine.

(Translated by Google) We ate in this place at noon, after 20 days in America, the first lunch that made us taste the Italian flavor again !! Very good pizza and linguine amatriciana!  (Original) Abbiamo mangiato in questo locale a mezzogiorno, dopo 20 giorni in America il primo pranzo che ci ha fatto riassaporare il sapore italiano!! Molto buona la pizza e le linguine all’amatriciana!
Always great food and Sandro is the best host and friend
Great place great food and very friendly workers

Came here with a large group of people for happy hour, and they handled it very well! Staff were friendly and efficient. Happy hour food was very affordable and tasty - recommend the calamari, pizza and meatballs. Burschetta was so so. Lots of families with smaller kids come here too, so there's a pretty homey vibe.
relaxing with good pizza
The Linguine Bolognese was delicious as were the pizzas and Tiramisu. Everything is made fresh and the service is very friendly. I highly recommend eating here if you are in the neighborhood ☺

Delicious, homemade Italian food paired with a friendly, welcoming staff, makes you feel like you're having dinner at a friend's place. Everything tastes clean and fresh never oily or too salty... Even as a person who generally bypasses Italian restaurants, I'll be stopping by Bettolona for a long time to come.
We attended a private party here so the food was determined by the host. I enjoyed the pizza but it was super light, so order two. Attractive space.

The restaurant is a mid-high scale Italian restaurant. The atmosphere is nice and they have great service; however, I don't think the food is worth the high price. We ordered a spinach lasagna, spaghetti and meatballs, salad, and linguini in clam sauce. The linguini was pretty dry and the clams were tiny (VERY tiny). The spaghetti could also use more sauce as well.
Friendly, good hours for after a show at MSM. Friendly staff. Very good food. Pizza is perfect.

Excellent service and a great place to go with your family! They bent over backwards to help us accommodate our 6 month old baby on a busy afternoon and the experience was great. The waiter was very friendly and gave us great recommendations. The food was delicious as well, in particular their pizzas. A great overall experience.
Nice place... delicious food! The servers are the best!! Good job
Fantastic atmosphere; the owner and the staff here go above and beyond to ensure a positive experience. I will happily return here again and again.

Quiet, good food, though can be right on the edge of salty.  Editing review after more visits: the saltiness hasn't been as pronounced, the wine list has some real gems, and the artichoke dish is addictively good. Most of all, however, the staff is the best!

Basically, I love this restaurant. However, the quality of waiters vary greatly. Experienced waiters here are all very nice. I love them. By contrast, new or short-term waiters here are often not well-trained. They have charged me more than it should have been, etc. The new female waiter who has started working around this week (?) seems to rush customers constantly during their dinner/lunch, even though it is not crowded and there is enough room for other customers to come. She walks around and around near the tables of customers incessantly and mutters to herself... to rush customers and get them out of the restaurant as soon as possible. It was even a little scary. A gentleman next to my table looked a little frightened... We come here to relax, please understand it!! (By the way, the food here is delicious, so I feel very sad about the poorly-trained waiters all the more... I have to steer away from the restaurant while those poor-trained waiters are working there).
One of my favorite Italian spots
Great pizza and pasta Friendly with good service

Delivery personnel was very rude. I went and paid at the restaurant. Half an hour later the delivery guy shows up but doesn't even come to the door and I have to approach him and ask him who the food is for and where it came from. He then responds are you Juan I say yes I am that's mine. He comes over and tells me 40 something. I say I already paid it at the restaurant. It's paid for I just need to give you your tips here. And he wouldn't take the tips. He said you won't get your food until you pay because that's not what they told me. I called the restaurant and talked to the manager. While I was talking to him he pulls my wireless headphones away and yanks them out my ear. And talks to the manager then gives them back after a few seconds and says sorry take your food and tells me to get it because he can't give it to me. I give him his tips $4 and he pulls the cash and still tells me to take my food out. I asked him to please take the pizza out since I had already taken the other bag and had two others. He took the pizza out and says take your damn pizza. Great food but horrible delivery staff.
Great food, in fact the food is so good I couldn't choose what to get on the menu! Great people, the boss is very nice. Would recommend and will go again
Recommend!!!
The food was great
Great value for good quality pizza
Nice caprese salad, Great pizza and an excellent glass of wine made for an excellent lunch
Nice place
Food is irrestible!! I can't stop coming here with my friends or family and I often order online.-
Nice people, relaxing ambience, most important - pizza was delicious. Fresh ingredients, priced fairly, and served promptly.
Good Italian food, pizza is good
Great Food, the artichoke appetizer the best appetizer I've ever had!
Best pizza in the neighborhood
Definitely my favorite Italian restaurant in the neighborhood.  The people there are kind and the food and wine are delicious.
Fantastic pizzas made in a brick oven!!! Real  New Yorker pizza style. Also good margaritas 😀
Amazing food, amazing people!!
Great service - do yourself a favor and get the prosciutto pizza. Will change your life.
Decent beer and food selection. Try their beer sample if you re not sure!
Nice Italian fresh pizza near Columbia University.
Lunch today was fantasic! Gnocchi! Thanks for a delicious meal!
Zero stars obvisiouly. Arguably the best pizza in NYC. Italian display of macho culture, where groping is considered fun. Zero star
Nice place for drinks. Also pizza is good.
overpriced food.
Great pizza and Sandro is the best host
Best original Italian Pizza and courteous service
Amazing pizza! Even the bread they give you is pizza-y.

Best pizza I've ever had. The oven in the middle of the restaurant let's you see your pizza crisp up and bubble. The dessert menu is equally delicious. The Bianca Pizza and Lemoncello Tartufo are second to none.
One of my favorite places. It's dangerous for me to have lasts this good within a block of my home.
Overpriced with terrible pizza. Paid $20 for a tiny pizza with cheese that slides right off and they don't even have pepperoni. I wish I had went with Digiorno.

Always feel like I'm at home when I come here. One of the best brick oven pizza spots in the city. The brunch on the weekend is well priced with great options. Menu items made with fresh ingredients, robust flavor and great service.

(Translated by Google) We have been in this magnificent restaurant this summer ... for 5 nights! In fact, my wife is ill-suited to non-Italian food. At the "Bettolona" we found really well cooked food, and really "Italian". In addition to food, the hospitality of the staff is truly exceptional. From the metro stop it is 100 meters on foot, over dinner in 15 minutes you were back in Times Square. Therefore highly recommended to those lucky enough to stay in New York.  (Original) Siamo stati in questo magnifico ristorante questa estate... per ben 5 sere ! Infatti mia moglie mal si adatta al cibo NON italico. Alla "Bettolona" abbiamo trovato cibo veramente ben cucinato, e veramente "italiano". Oltre al cibo, l'accoglienza dello staff è veramente eccezionale. Dalla fermata della metropolitana sono 100 mt a piedi, finita cena in 15 minuti si era nuovamente in Times Square. Consigliatissimo quindi a chi avrà la fortuna di soggiornare a New York.

We had a perfect lunch, italian manager Michele is the living proof that italians are not the ones who scream , not the ones from a 1950 movie, but the masters of elegance and knowledge ! Suggested!!!

Went here with my birthday with a part of 12 people. They had a huge table ready for us and were accommodating with our many orders. Great food and it really tastes Italian. Definitely recommend it and it's pretty affordable especially for how amazing the food is.

Awesome place. Very solid pastas, good pizzas. The pizzas are Italian style, small, charred in a wood burning oven that is in the dining area. It adds to the warm ambiance. The decor is rustic and cool, lowly lit with hanging Edison bulbs. The prices are really great, less than 15 bucks for pastas, same for pizzas. The wine is extremely low priced- $20 bucks for a bottle of the house red or white, and the red was decent.  The service is really great also, everyone was very nice and they gave us free limoncello shots after dinner. The only drawback is the location, the walk to the 125th Street 1 train isn't lovely at night, and a cab to anywhere but the UWS will run you a nice chunk of change. Otherwise really solid place, I will definitely return.

I really enjoy dining at this Italian restaurant. It has a very nice atmosphere and the large floor to ceiling windows open up in the summer to let in a cool breeze. It has nice neighborhood feel and is a great gem in Morningside Heights.
Bettelona is the best! Their pizzas are delicious, and always fresh. They have authentic italian food, that always hits the spot. service is also great!
NEVER order pizza delivery from them. We waited for 50 minutes just to get 3 cold pizzas for $40+.
